The paper deals with the outage performance of MIMO channels, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM). The focus on machine-type communication (cMTC) also suggests a possible connection to networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The analysis of the spatial correlation effects in the MIMO channel matrix involves linear algebra and system theory, which could fall under systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the use of analytical results to guide MIMO configuration design suggests a possible connection to machine learning and optimization (cs.MA).
